{"id":"hebrew-of-the-hebrews","term":"Hebrew of the Hebrews","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>One whose parents are both Hebrews (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Philippians 3:5\">Phil. 3:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Corinthians 11:22\">2 Cor. 11:22</a>); a genuine Hebrew.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Philippians 3:5","2 Corinthians 11:22"]}